<parameter name="new_string">    helpText: 'Regular performance practice builds stamina, concentration, and confidence while simulating real performance conditions that reveal technical and mental preparation gaps. Set aside time each week to play through your repertoire continuously without pausing to correct mistakes, focusing on maintaining musical flow and composure even when errors occur, which develops the performance mindset essential for sharing your music with others.'
  },
  {
    id: 'prompt-44',
    prompt: 'Practice improvisation exercises over basic chord progressions for 10 minutes daily using scales you\'ve learned',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Improvisation develops musical creativity, deepens understanding of scales and chords, and builds confidence in spontaneous musical expression. Start with simple 2-3 chord progressions in keys you know well, use pentatonic or major scales to create short melodic phrases over the changes, and focus on listening to how different notes sound against each chord to develop your musical ear and creative expression skills.'
  }
];</parameter>
